    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="547"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <head>547. Memorandum of meeting of the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                    Executive Committee by <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName>, November
                        19<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d547fn1">Cuban contingency plan of
                        November 19; proposed messages to <persName corresp="#p_dGGC_1">de
                            Gaulle</persName>, Adenauer, and <persName corresp="#p_MH_1"
                            >Macmillan</persName>; proposed resolution to <gloss target="#t_OAS_1"
                            >OAS</gloss>; President’s press conference. Top Secret. 1 p. <gloss
                            target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_DCI_1">DCI</gloss>
                            (<persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName>) Files: Job
                        80–B01285A.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-11-19T18:00:00">November 19, 1962, 6
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d547-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d547-1"/>
                <p>The following were considered:</p>
                <p>1. A tentative draft of the task force working on Cuban contingency plan dated
                    11/19 was reviewed, modified and <gloss target="#t_SecDef_1">SecDef</gloss>
                    agreed to resubmit a redraft of Part II for further consideration.</p>
                <p>2. Proposed message to DeGaulle, Adenauer and <persName corresp="#p_MH_1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> was reviewed, modified and approved.</p>
                <p>3. Proposed resolution to the <gloss target="#t_OAS_1">OAS</gloss> was reviewed,
                    and it was decided that the <gloss target="#t_OAS_1">OAS</gloss> meeting should
                    be “informative”, and in all probability a resolution should not be
                    submitted.</p>
                <p>4. Briefing paper for President’s press conference was not considered pending
                    receipt of written statement by <persName corresp="#p_STC_1"
                    >Sorensen</persName>.</p>
                <p>Note: On Tuesday morning <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName> took
                    exception to the attached Questions and Answers on the grounds that they
                    provided too much of an implied endorsement of Castro, and therefore would
                    disenfranchise the United States from many <gloss target="#t_OAS_1">OAS</gloss>
                    states.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_MJA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">John A. McCone</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <affiliation>Director</affiliation>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
